\par\par French (adj.法国的) historical author Patrick Modiano (n.莫迪亚诺) has won the 2014 Nobel (n.诺贝尔（奖）) Prize for literature (n.文学).\par\par 　　The Nobel Academy (n.学院) described the novelist (n.小说家), whose work has often focused (v.关注) on the Nazi (n.纳粹) occupation (n.占领（地区）) of France (n.法国), as 'a Marcel Proust (n.普鲁斯特) of our time'.\par\par 　　At a press conference (n.记者 招待会) in Paris (n.巴黎), the publicity(n.传媒关注)-shy (adj.躲避的) Modiano expressed his surprise at the win and said he was keen (adj.渴望的) to find out why he was chosen.\par\par 　　"I wasn't expecting (v.预料) it at all," he said. "It was like I was a bit detached (adj.无动于衷的) from it all, as if a doppelganger (n.相貌一样的人) with my name had won."\par\par 　　Modiano beat (v.击败) bookies(n.赌博庄家)' favourites (n.热门人选) Japanese (adj.日本的) writer Haruki Murakami (n.村上春树) and Kenyan (adj.肯尼亚的) novelist, poet (n.诗人) and playwright (n.剧作家) Ngugi wa Thiong'o (n.提昂戈). The last French writer to win the prize was Jean-Marie Gustave Le Clezio (n.勒克莱齐奥) in 2008.\par\par 　　The academy said the award was "for the art of memory with which he has evoked (v.唤起) the most ungraspable (adj.无法抓住的) human destinies (n.命运) and uncovered (v.揭露) the life-world (n.生活世界) of the occupation".\par\par (BBC, October 9)--------------------------------------------------　　法国历史作家莫迪亚诺，赢得了二○一四年诺贝尔文学奖。\par\par 　　这位小说家的作品，经常关注纳粹占领法国的一段历史，诺贝尔学院形容他是「我们这个时代的普鲁斯特」。\par\par 　　在巴黎的记者 招待会上，一向不惯面对传媒的莫迪亚诺表示对得奖感到惊讶，并说自己很想知道他为何当选。\par\par 　　「我丝毫没有预料得到。」他说。「这好像我对这一切有点无动于衷，就像一个相貌和名字跟我一样的人赢了。」\par\par 　　莫迪亚诺击败了庄家热门人选――日本作家村上春树，及肯尼亚小说家、诗人兼剧作家提昂戈。上次获得这个奖项的法国作家，是二○○八年的勒克莱齐奥。\par\par 　　学院指出，这个奖项「旨在颂赞记忆的艺术，他借此唤起了最无法抓住的人类命运，并揭露了占领地区的生活世界」。\par\par （英国广播公司，十月九日）\par\par 1.	occupation (n) /'kj?'peI??n/，ock-kew-PAY-shun 占领、占据\par\par 知多点：被某国家或军队占领，前面常用介系词under，例如UFrance has been under German occupation during the Second World War（法国在二次大战期间被德军占领）；动词是occupy，例如「\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b\cf6 占领中环\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b0\cf0 」运动便叫\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b\cf6 Occupy Central\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b0\cf0 。\par\par 2.	detached (adj) /dI'tat?t/，dit-TATCH-t 无动于衷的、置身事外的\par\par 知多点：动词detach本指脱离、摆脱，例如UThe little boy detached himself from his mother's embrace（那小男孩挣脱了他母亲的拥抱）；过去分词detached常用作形容词，并常引申指心理上的脱离，亦即无动于衷的、置身事外的。\par\par 3.	ungraspable (adj) /Λn'gr:sp?bl/，un-GRASP-pa-bl 无法抓住的、难以领悟的\par\par 知多点：动词grasp解作抓住、捉紧，例如grasp her shoulders with his hands是用他双手抓紧她的肩膀；在前面加上表示不、否的un-，在后面加上表示可以、能够的-able，便解作无法抓住的，并引申指难以领悟的。\par\par Q&A\par\par 请把下列5个英文字填在句子的横线上，并使用适当的单复数时态等。\par\par destiny　  detach　  favourite　  occupation　  ungraspable\par\par 1. Staying _____ while witnessing injustice is not right.\par\par 2. He is the red-hot _____ to win the contest.\par\par 3. During the _____, many churches were used as mosques.\par\par 4. She always wanted to be in control of her own _____.\par\par 5. I find his arguments quite _____.\par\par Answers\par\par 1. detached　2. favourite　3. occupation　4. destiny　5. ungraspable\par\par 文：范斌\par\par  \par
