ng their footprints in Hong Kong. \par\par The mid-tier brands are expected to  benefit from several optimistic market  factors such as sophisticated consumers  who are looking for more mid-priced  or affordable luxury products. \par\par Underpinning this is a low employment rate of about 3.4 percent and a  positive local consumer market. \par\par Joanne Lee is manager of research  and advisory at Colliers International.  Contact her at joanne.lee@colliers.com  \par
