han the stocks can go,” Govertsen said.\par\par The slide is likely to continue into October as the local government rolls out stricter enforcement of a smoking ban on mass market casino floors, starting yesterday, and \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b\cf6 Occupy Central\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b0\cf0  protests in Hong Kong reduce the number of mainland visitors.\par\par \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b\cf6 Occupy Central\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b0\cf0  protests that began in Hong Kong on September 28, ahead of the National Day holiday have weakened mainland tourist numbers because visitors have increasingly been combining visits to Hong Kong and Macau in one trip. The Travel Industry Council of Macau warned that fewer mainland visitors would visit both cities.\par\par “It used to be that mainlanders would go to either Hong Kong or Macau but a lot more are doing a triangle,” Andrew Scott, group chief executive of consultancy World Gaming said.\par\par  \par
