cupymovement has virtually confirmed its long-time fearof a colour revolution.\par\par Though news about the Occupy movement isblocked on the mainland, it is impossible to preventmessages about it from being circulated on theInternet. Mainlanders' messages of support for themovement, for example, were projected from someoccupied locations. The central government's realworry is that the affair may have repercussions onthe mainland. Its judgment coloured by itsunderstanding and reading of the situation in theSAR, the central government may be of the opinionthat the Occupy protests will not only damage HongKong's law and order but also potentially threatenthe mainland's stability. In this light, we do not seethe central government has much room for treatingthe protests leniently. It has, we believe, a strongmotive for taking tough action to keep things undercontrol and end the crisis as soon as possible.\par\par The Occupy movement began with classboycotts. That the students have been stressingthe need to stay peaceful, rational and non-violentis the reason why so many citizens have beenimpelled to support them in person. The legitimacyof the movement will be challenged if the HongKong Federation of Students chooses to clash withthe police. The Occupy movement has made itinconvenient for citizens to go about their lives orbusiness. School classes in the Central andWestern District and in Wan Chai are stillsuspended, and no one can tell when they willresume. Stores and newsagents in occupiedlocations have seen their business hugely affected.Political unrest in Hong Kong has sent a plunge toevery financial market, with the Hong Kong dollarand the stock market continuously under pressure.\par\par It is already investors' concern that a financial stormmay be looming. The situation will worsen with thepassage of time and the prolongation of the crisis,and it is expected that sooner or later the tide ofpublic opinion will turn. The Federation and theOccupy Central trio should think about how theyshould reap the rewards of their effort and figureout their future plans rather than ponder how toclash with or oppose the police.\par\par 英语社评声档english.mingpao.com/critic.htm\par\par 事态滑向危险边缘各方万勿火上加油\par\par 明报社评\par\par 占领行动事态，未因为过去数日情势稍为平静而有良性转机，反而恶化。各方若继续一意孤行，新一轮警方与示威者冲突，甚至更暴烈的对抗，极有可能发生。\par\par 发起占领行动的学联和\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b\cf6 占中\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b0\cf0 发起人，要求特首梁振英辞职和全国人大常委会撤回政改决定。中央连日透过中央电视台、《人民日报》和新华社三大官方喉舌，分别以报道和评论员文章，高调支持梁振英和特区政府，同时支持警方依法处置违法行为。至于人大常委会的决定，也都表明绝对不会撤回。中央明确表态，是要杜绝反对阵营有丝毫幻想。从中央的角度，对事态的疑虑不止于香港内部情况，还有外部对事态的关注与回响。\par\par 美国、英国高度关注此事。美国总统奥巴马、英国首相卡梅伦分别开腔，英美传媒大篇幅重点报道，其中把事态描述为「雨伞革命」，相信会触动中央的神经。因为公民抗命性质是自我牺牲的社会运动，革命对任何政权而言，都是不得了的挑战。若香港发生的是一场革命，那是要推翻特区政府还是中央政府？对于中央而言，西方传媒对占领行动的定性，中央一直忧疑的颜色革命，宛如得到印证。\par\par 另外，内地虽然封锁占领行动的信息，但是互联网世界不可能完全阻绝这类信息在内地流传；有内地人士的支援短讯在占领场地投射出来，就中央而言，事态会否辐射到内地，成为实质忧疑。从中央的角度，对香港事态的认知和解读，或许认为占领行动不单使香港失控失序、对大陆的稳定也构成潜在风险。因此，中央对香港事态的处理，看不到有宽松空间，反而有强力掌控、尽快解决事态的动机。\par\par 这场占领行动，由学生罢课开始，触动那么多市民以行动支持占领，主要是学生强调和平、理性、非暴力，若学联选择与警方冲突，则它的正当性会受到质疑。占领行动对市民生活、工作引起不便，中西区和湾仔的学校复课无期，占领区附近商铺与报摊等小商贩生意大受影响，而因为政局动荡，整体市道下滑，港元汇率、股市持续下跌，会否引发金融风暴已经成为投资者的悬念。随着时日推移，若事态延宕，这些影响将会深化下去。可以预期，民意逆转可能只是早晚的事，学联与\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b\cf6 占中\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\f15 \b0\cf0 三子应该思考如何收割已经取得的成果，徐图后计，而非寻思与警方冲突对抗。\par\par Glossary\par\par stick to one's own gunsrefuse to change one's mind even when othersare trying to persuade one that one is wrongillusion /??lu:?n/false idea or belief, especially about somebodyor a situationloom /lu:m/appear threatening and likely to happen soon \par
